- Linux http://www.cpantesters.org/cpan/report/d90bc1c8-f86b-11df-9081-1b18960acfcc
gtk/iupgtk_button.c: In function 'gtkButtonMapMethod':
gtk/iupgtk_button.c:454:5: warning: implicit declaration of function 'GTK_OBJECT_FLAGS'
gtk/iupgtk_button.c:454:5: error: lvalue required as left operand of assignment
A workaround is to add
  #define GTK_OBJECT_FLAGS(obj)             (GTK_OBJECT (obj)->flags)
right before the lines where these two errors occur.

iupgtk_button.c patch:
-GTK_WIDGET_FLAGS(ih->handle) &= ~GTK_CAN_FOCUS;
+GTK_OBJECT(ih->handle)->flags &= ~GTK_CAN_FOCUS;

from: http://library.gnome.org/devel/gtk/2.21/GtkWidget.html
GTK_WIDGET_FLAGS has been deprecated since version 2.20 and should not be used in newly-written code.

